-----BEGIN SQLTRIAGE UPDATE SIGNING KEY PLACEHOLDER-----
This is NOT a real public key. It is a placeholder shipped so the build
compiles before the Authenticode code-signing certificate is available.

While this placeholder is in place, UpdateSignatureVerifier.IsTrustedKeyConfigured
returns false and ALL update-signature checks FAIL CLOSED (no update can be
staged or applied). Combined with "Updates:Enabled": false in client/test
appsettings, the updater is fully inert.

TO GO LIVE (drop-in once you have the cert):
  1. tools\extract-update-pubkey.ps1 -Pfx <your-codesigning>.pfx
     -> overwrites this file with the real SubjectPublicKeyInfo PEM
        (-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY----- ... -----END PUBLIC KEY-----)
  2. Rebuild (the real key is embedded into the assembly).
  3. Release with: publish-release.ps1 -SigningPfx <path> -SigningPassword <pwd>
  4. Set "Updates:Enabled": true in the shipped config/appsettings.json.

The verifier auto-detects RSA or ECDSA from the PEM, so any standard
code-signing certificate works without code changes.
-----END SQLTRIAGE UPDATE SIGNING KEY PLACEHOLDER-----
